CSS Lists

Lists in HTML are of two types:

1. Ordered List (<ol>)

Displays numbers.

<ol>
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>React</li>
</ol>

Output

1. Java
2. Python
3. React
2. Unordered List (<ul>)

Displays bullets.

<ul>
    <li>Apple</li>
    <li>Mango</li>
    <li>Orange</li>
</ul>

Output

• Apple
• Mango
• Orange
CSS List Properties

There are mainly 3 properties you should know.

1. list-style-type
2. list-style-position
3. list-style-image
1. list-style-type ⭐⭐⭐

Changes the bullet or numbering style.

Syntax
list-style-type: value;
Example 1 : Disc (Default)
.disc{
    list-style-type: disc;
}

Output

• Apple
• Mango
• Orange
Example 2 : Circle
.circle{
    list-style-type: circle;
}

Output

○ Apple
○ Mango
○ Orange
  
Example 3 : Square
.square{
    list-style-type: square;
}

Output

■ Apple
■ Mango
■ Orange
Example 4 : None

Removes bullets.

.none{
    list-style-type: none;
}

Output

Apple
Mango
Orange

